Description:
   Checkpoint Break is a fundamental Warden offensive technique. The warrior
   drives a powerful headbutt or shoulder charge into the opponent, targeting
   their guard and breaking through their defensive positioning. The attack
   deals physical damage and can momentarily stagger the target.

   As the Warden's earliest active combat skill, Checkpoint Break serves as
   a bread-and-butter melee attack that supplements regular weapon strikes.
   The blow is forceful enough to interrupt spellcasting when it connects,
   making it valuable against caster opponents. The technique requires the
   Warden to commit to a forward rush, leaving them briefly vulnerable if
   the attack misses.
